{erg \\, s^{-1}}$, in the hyper-luminous X-ray sources (HLXs) regime, are\nreached by $\\sim 7\\%$ of the IMBHs. These findings suggest that HLXs are a\nsmall subset of the wandering IMBH population, which is characterized by\nluminosities $10^3-10^4$ times fainter. Dedicated surveys are needed to assess\nthe demographics of this missing population of black holes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 28 Oct 2022 18:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 2 Apr 2023 21:57:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-04"}
