 limit when the radial\ncoordinate is held fixed. The behavior of the symmetric two-point function when\nthe field is in the Unruh state is investigated for the case of a delta\nfunction potential in certain asymptotically flat black hole spacetimes in two\ndimensions. The removal of the infrared divergences in the mode functions\nresults in the elimination of terms that grow linearly in time.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 28 Oct 2022 20:38:25 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 22 Nov 2022 21:36:28 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 7 Jun 2023 16:48:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-06-08"}
