 coupling properties preserved. A\nfurther $\\approx$~10$\\times$ reduction of $V$ by defect localization is\nobserved in rod PhCRs. Moreover, both fundamental and 2nd-order PhC modes\nco-exist in slit PhCRs with high $Q$s and good coupling. Our work showcases\nthat high-$Q/V$ PhCRs are in general straightforward to design and fabricate\nand are a promising platform to explore for cQED.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 28 Oct 2022 23:34:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-01"}
