\nthat the catechol molecule gets desorbed from the pristine biphenylene sheet\neven at 100 K but remains attached to metal (Pd, Ti) decorated biphenylene\nsheets at room temperature by performing the ab-initio molecular dynamics\nsimulations. The Ti-decorated biphenylene sheet has more sensitivity toward\ncatechol adsorption while the Pd-decorated biphenylene sheet has a suitable\nrecovery time at 500 K. The results suggest that the Pd and Ti-decorated\nbiphenylene sheets are promising materials for catechol detection.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 29 Oct 2022 03:49:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-01"}
